en_403529_0	Colonel D.K.S.K Dolage assumed duties as the 9th Commander of the 571 Brigade on Wednesday (4) September during a simple ceremony at the 571 Brigade Headquarters in Kilinochchi.
en_403529_1	A formal Guard Turnout at the entrance, presented by 7 Sri Lanka Light Infantry troops greeted him.
en_403529_2	He left his signature in a formal document and symbolized the occasion.
en_403529_3	Afterwards, the newly-appointed Brigade Commander planted a Mango sapling in the compound as a symbol of memory before he joined a customary troop address and an all rank tea.
en_403529_4	Commanding Officer of the 7 Sri Lanka Light Infantry & 9 Vijayabhau Infantry Regiment and Brigade Staff Officers attended the occasion.
